<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-92-1088 </DOCNO><TEXT>This paper summarizes and discusses the national PCB-spill-cleanup policy.The policy requires that all new PCB spills be cleaned up according tostrict performance standards. All professionals responsible for PCB managementshould be familiar with this policy, since it once again changes thegame rules for handling PCBs. This summary addresses and clarifies thePCB-policy's requirements for spill reporting, cleanup, post-cleanupsampling, and record-keeping, along with some of the policy's problemsand implications. 4 references, 1 table.</TEXT></DOC>